title: Celebrating the Holiday Season in Space
description: Crew members aboard the International Space Station celebrate the holiday season in a unique way while living and working at the orbiting laboratory. Each crew member, including the current Expedition 72, spends time enjoying the view of Earth from the space station, privately communicating with their friends and families, and sharing a joint meal with […]
author: Andrea Dunn

title: Commercial Moon Rovers Under Test
description: Venturi Astrolab’s FLEX, Intuitive Machines’ Moon RACER, and Lunar Outpost’s Eagle lunar terrain vehicle – three commercially owned and developed LTVs (Lunar Terrain Vehicle) – are pictured at NASA’s Johnson Space Center in Houston in this photo from Nov. 21, 2024. author: Monika Luabeya

title: NASA’s Mars helicopter was grounded in 2024 after surprise success
description: The Ingenuity autonomous helicopter surpassed all expectations to fly dozens of missions over several years on the Red Planet, only stopping this year when an accident damaged one of its rotors

title: The best space images from 2024
description: This year has delivered some awe-inspiring imagery of space, from the James Webb Space Telescope’s stunning shots of faraway stars and galaxies to images of the skies taken from here on planet Earth

title: Scientists hope NASA's Parker Solar Probe gets hit by a storm during historic Christmas Eve sun flyby
description: If all goes to plan, the sun should give NASA's Parker Solar Probe a hard time.

title: See a dead Chinese satellite burn up as a brilliant fireball in the night sky (video)
description: The satellite was one of China's first-ever commercial Earth imaging satellites. RIP, SuperView 1-02.

title: Starwatch: Mercury reaches greatest western elongation
description: As this elusive inner planet orbits its furthest from the sun westwards, it will be visible in the morning sky Get your Christmas started with a celestial achievement by tracking down the inner planet Mercury early in the morning.Because of its tight orbit, Mercury never appears far from the sun. This makes it a challenging object to observe because it never appears in a fully dark sky, only close to the horizon during twilight. Continue reading...
author: Stuart Clark

title: Nasa astronauts stuck in space since June face further delay
description: Return pushed back to late March, stretching mission that was supposed to last eight days to more than nine monthsThe two Nasa astronauts who have been stuck in space since June because of technical issues will have to remain at the International Space Station even longer – stretching a mission that was originally supposed to last only eight days to more than nine months.On Tuesday, Nasa announced that its astronauts Suni Williams and Butch Wilmore, along with Russia’s cosmonaut Aleksandr Gorbunov, will return to Earth following the arrival of Crew-10 next year. Originally scheduled for a February launch, the space agency has pushed back the Crew-10 mission’s launch date to no earlier than late March of 2025. Continue reading...
author: Maya Yang in New York
